jobs.jobCommentText: Scale stuck at zero,  will not read weight
jobs.jobWorkPerformed:
Customer reported scale (1664700128) to not be registering any weight. Hsc checked load cell and homerun cable at junction box and found 1.5V out of 10v on excitation wires. Hsc then checked each wire one by one and found that one load cell to have continuity between both excitation wires, as well as very low ohm readings. Hsc could not effectively trace back load cell due to run of wire through pipe so technician needed to check every cell to eliminate others. Hsc did find two niches on two different load cell and eliminated all and re-ran wire. With the niche removed from last load cell, the excitation wires were no longer in continuity with each other but still reading bad on OHM and MV readings. HSC also waited for other scale company for calibration. Customer will need new load cell.
Call Incomplete
